{"title": "Japan faces inauspicious start to new year with resilience", "tags": "asia", "timestamp": "2024-01-04", "content": "TOKYO \u2013 Just four days into 2024, calamity (\u707d) is already a front-runner for when Japan chooses its word of the year come December.\nFirst, a devastating earthquake, then a fiery plane collision at Japan\u2019s busiest airport. These were followed by an inferno that razed Japan\u2019s oldest shopping arcade, and then a random stabbing incident on a public train."}